   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE CONCERNING THE DIVINE TRINITY 3 Scripture Reading: 1 Cor 15:45b; 2 Cor 3:17; Rev 1:4; Isa 9:6; Heb 1:3; Col 1:15; Rev 5:6 OUTLINE The creeds: The Apostles' Creed.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The Nicene Creed.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>A Revision of the Nicene Creed.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The Chalcedonian Confession of Faith.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The Athanasian Creed.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>A heresy in the creeds the Mother of God Theotokos .</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The inadequacy of the creeds: The last Adam becoming the life-giving Spirit 1 Cor 15:45b.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Lord being the Spirit 2 Cor 3:17.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The seven Spirits Rev 1:4; 3:1; 4:5; 5:6.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The Son being called the Eternal Father Isa 9:6.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The coinherence of the Father, the Son, and the Spirit John 14:10, 20; 10:38; 17:21, 23.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The Son being the effulgence of God's glory and the impress of God's substance Heb 1:3; Col 1:15a; 2 Cor 4:4.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The Spirit being the eyes of the Son Rev 5:6; Zech 3:9; 4:10.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The Son as the Angel of Jehovah; as Jehovah, the self-existing and ever-existing One; and as Elohim, the Triune God Exo 3:2-15; 14:19; 23:20-21; Judg.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>13:15-21; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Rev 7:2; 8:3; 10:1; 18:1.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The Son as the One sent by Jehovah and as Jehovah, the Sender Zech 2:8-11.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>When Christ, the Son, was baptized, the Spirit descending upon Him; when He died, God forsaking Him Matt 3:16; 27:46.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The Son being the only begotten Son of the Father and the firstborn Son of God John 1:18; 3:18; Rom 8:29.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The Son being the Firstborn of all creation Col 1:15b.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The blood shed by the Son in His humanity being called the blood of God's Son and God's own blood 1 John 1:7; Acts 20:28.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Christ being the mystery of God and in Him all the fullness of the entire Godhead the Father, the Son, and the Spirit dwelling bodily Col 2:2, 9.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Christ, the Son, being the embodiment of the fullness of the divinity of the entire Triune God Col 2:9.</S>
   </TEXT>
